    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUnder the documentation for `:h diagnostic-handlers-example` there is a handy example for reducing the number diagnostics shown per-line that looks like:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n    -- Create a custom namespace. This will aggregate signs from all other\r\n    -- namespaces and only show the one with the highest severity on a\r\n    -- given line\r\n    local ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"my_namespace\")\r\n\r\n    -- Get a reference to the original signs handler\r\n    local orig_signs_handler = vim.diagnostic.handlers.signs\r\n\r\n    -- Override the built-in signs handler\r\n    vim.diagnostic.handlers.signs = {\r\n      show = function(_, bufnr, _, opts)\r\n        -- Get all diagnostics from the whole buffer rather than just the\r\n        -- diagnostics passed to the handler\r\n        local diagnostics = vim.diagnostic.get(bufnr)\r\n\r\n        -- Find the \"worst\" diagnostic per line\r\n        local max_severity_per_line = {}\r\n        for _, d in pairs(diagnostics) do\r\n          local m = max_severity_per_line[d.lnum]\r\n          if not m or d.severity < m.severity then\r\n            max_severity_per_line[d.lnum] = d\r\n          end\r\n        end\r\n\r\n        -- Pass the filtered diagnostics (with our custom namespace) to\r\n        -- the original handler\r\n        local filtered_diagnostics = vim.tbl_values(max_severity_per_line)\r\n        orig_signs_handler.show(ns, bufnr, filtered_diagnostics, opts)\r\n      end,\r\n      hide = function(_, bufnr)\r\n        orig_signs_handler.hide(ns, bufnr)\r\n      end,\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen at least two lines are removed, and there is a line following them that has a severity of at least error, it results in:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1328: Invalid 'line': out of range\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1328: in function 'show'\r\n        ~/.config/nvim_severity_test/init.lua:28: in function 'show'\r\n        ~/.config/nvim_severity_test/plugin/diagnostics.lua:43: in function 'show'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1684: in function 'show'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1031: in function 'set'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua:260: in function 'handle_diagnostics'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua:293: in function 'handler'\r\n        /opt/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:1005: in function ''\r\n        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\r\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. create `~/.config/nvim_severity_test/init.lua`:\r\n    ```lua\r\n    vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\r\n      pattern = \"lua\",\r\n      callback = function()\r\n        vim.lsp.start({\r\n          name = \"lua_ls\",\r\n          cmd = { \"lua-language-server\" },\r\n          root_dir = vim.fn.getcwd(),\r\n        })\r\n      end,\r\n    })\r\n    \r\n    local ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"my_namespace\")\r\n    local orig_signs_handler = vim.diagnostic.handlers.signs\r\n    vim.diagnostic.handlers.signs = {\r\n      show = function(_, bufnr, _, opts)\r\n        local diagnostics = vim.diagnostic.get(bufnr)\r\n        local max_severity_per_line = {}\r\n        for _, d in pairs(diagnostics) do\r\n          local m = max_severity_per_line[d.lnum]\r\n          if not m or d.severity < m.severity then\r\n            max_severity_per_line[d.lnum] = d\r\n          end\r\n        end\r\n        local filtered_diagnostics = vim.tbl_values(max_severity_per_line)\r\n        orig_signs_handler.show(ns, bufnr, filtered_diagnostics, opts)\r\n      end,\r\n      hide = function(_, bufnr)\r\n        orig_signs_handler.hide(ns, bufnr)\r\n      end,\r\n    }\r\n    ```\r\n2. create `test_case.lua`\r\n    ```lua\r\n    -- 1. line to delete\r\n    -- 2. line to delete\r\n    syntax error\r\n    ```\r\n3. open Neovim with `NVIM_APPNAME=nvim_severity_test nvim test_case.lua`\r\n4. wait a moment for the LSP server to report diagnostics\r\n5. delete the comment block in one go with `dgc`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo crash.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTerminal.app/tmux 3.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nMacPorts",
